eural crest cells","Cortex develops from neural crest cells and medulla from mesoderm","Cortex develops from mesoderm and medulla from neural crest cells","Cortex develops from endoderm and medulla from mesoderm"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe adrenal gland has two distinct embryological origins that reflect its dual function as an endocrine organ:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth cortex and medulla develop from mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E - This is incorrect as only the cortex is derived from mesoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoth cortex and medulla develop from neural crest cells\u003C/strong\u003E - Only the medulla originates from neural crest cells\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECortex develops from neural crest cells and medulla from mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the reverse of the correct arrangement\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECortex develops from mesoderm and medulla from neural crest cells\u003C/strong\u003E - This is correct. The cortex develops from intermediate mesoderm and coelomic epithelium, while the medulla forms from neural crest cells that migrate into the developing cortex\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECortex develops from endoderm and medulla from mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E - Neither component develops from endoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis dual embryological origin explains the distinct functions: the cortex produces steroid hormones while the medulla produces catecholamines.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The adrenal cortex develops from mesoderm, specifically from the intermediate mesoderm and coelomic epithelium","The adrenal medulla develops from neural crest cells, which are of ectodermal origin","The dual embryological origin of the adrenal gland reflects its distinct endocrine functions"],"references":["Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., 